As of the census of 2010, there were 299 people, 111 households, and 85 families residing in the CDP. There were 127 housing units, of which 16, or 12.6%, were vacant. The racial makeup of the CDP was 99.0% [[White Americans|white]] and 1.0% from two or more races. None of the population were [[Hispanic]] or [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Latino]] of any race.<ref name="Census 2010 DP">{{Cite web| url=https://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_SF1/SF1DP1/1600000US3348740| title=Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics: 2010 Census Summary File 1 (DP-1): Milton Mills CDP, New Hampshire| publisher=U.S. Census Bureau| work=American Factfinder| accessdate=October 24, 2017| archive-url=https://archive.today/20200213131628/https://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_SF1/SF1DP1/1600000US3348740| archive-date=February 13, 2020| url-status=dead}}</ref>

Of the 226 households in the CDP, 38.7% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 60.4% were headed by married couples living together, 13.5% had a female householder with no husband present, and 23.4% were non-families. 18.9% of all households were made up of individuals, and 6.3% were someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 2.69, and the average family size was 3.05.<ref name="Census 2010 DP"/>

26.4% of residents in the CDP were under the age of 18, 8.2% were from age 18 to 24, 22.4% were from 25 to 44, 31.1% were from 45 to 64, and 12.0% were 65 years of age or older. The median age was 40.4 years. For every 100 females, there were 74.9 males. For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 80.3 males.<ref name="Census 2010 DP"/>

